WEBVTT

00:00.514 --> 00:01.419
Thank you, Mary.

00:01.479 --> 00:02.183
Thank you so much.

00:02.645 --> 00:06.002
Okay, so let me get that going again.

00:06.370 --> 00:14.118
If you had forgotten, I'll remind you, at the beginning of this year, we are looking about rooted.

00:14.478 --> 00:26.410
It's a series we call rooted, and it's about exploring what it means to be planted in Christ, nourished by Him and growing, like a tree that bears fruit at the right time.

00:27.231 --> 00:31.095
And our key passage has been Psalm 1.

00:32.056 --> 00:33.778
And so I'm just going to read

00:33.858 --> 00:34.300
to you.

00:34.340 --> 00:40.120
I think it's the first four verses, which is where we've kind of sat ourselves at the beginning of this year.

00:40.160 --> 00:45.458
Blessed is the one who does not walk in step with the wicked

00:45.538 --> 00:55.639
or stand in the way that sinners take or sit in the company of mockers, but whose delight is in the law of the Lord and who meditates on his Lord day and night.

00:56.180 --> 01:07.122
That person is like a tree planted by streams of water which yields its fruit in season and whose leaf does not wither, whatever they do prospers.

01:08.034 --> 01:14.667
like a tree planted by streams of water which yields its fruit in season and whose leaf doesn't wither.

01:15.009 --> 01:16.818
Whatever they do, prospers.

01:17.506 --> 01:25.198
Years ago, Dave and I lived in a house, in Nottingham, and in the garden, it had the most beautiful plum tree.

01:25.298 --> 01:32.930
And you know that time of year where you could just walk down the garden and pick a big juicy Victoria plum, and it was absolutely incredible.

01:33.030 --> 01:36.856
It was like bending under the weight of the fruit that it produced.

01:37.016 --> 01:37.837
It was incredible.

01:38.679 --> 01:43.506
And God creates plum trees to bear fruit.

01:43.906 --> 01:47.491
And God creates us to bear fruit of all kinds.

01:48.192 --> 01:53.680
God created you and me to bear good fruit in our lives.

01:54.220 --> 01:56.644
Now, we are not going to sprout apples or plums.

01:56.844 --> 01:58.266
This is not going to happen.

01:58.727 --> 02:01.931
But our lives are created to produce fruit.

02:02.792 --> 02:04.314
Fruit, that is going to last.

02:04.975 --> 02:05.075
Okay?

02:05.696 --> 02:06.898
So I thought,

02:07.074 --> 02:09.737
That's a bit of a kind of abstract thought, isn't it really?

02:09.757 --> 02:12.259
So I wanna explain what does that mean?

02:12.299 --> 02:16.904
That fruit in our lives that's gonna last before I kick off a bit further.

02:17.405 --> 02:24.131
So I was thinking, the kind of fruit that I'm talking about in our lives are fruits of different sorts.

02:24.732 --> 02:26.494
So I don't know if you can see that, I hope you can.

02:26.874 --> 02:29.537
So I was thinking, there is kind of character fruit.

02:29.817 --> 02:33.061
You know, that kind of inner change, like who are we becoming?

02:33.621 --> 02:34.482
And very,

02:34.530 --> 02:42.379
brilliantly, obviously, Galatians 5 talks about the fruit of the Spirit of God working in us means that we are changing.

02:42.399 --> 02:56.395
The fruit in our lives when internally we are changing and we are really rooted in Jesus is that we see more love, patience, joy, peace, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, self-control.

02:56.855 --> 03:01.040
That's the inner, that character fruit that goes on deep in us.

03:01.801 --> 03:02.962
Then maybe there's like

03:03.074 --> 03:08.765
life fruit that people can see from the outside is how we actually live.

03:09.366 --> 03:21.810
The fruit might look like serving others, it might look like forgiving quickly, it might be speaking the truth with grace, it might be sharing generously, it might be that you have real integrity.

03:22.786 --> 03:25.510
or maybe relational relationship fruit.

03:25.651 --> 03:27.493
You know that impact that you have on others.

03:28.154 --> 03:29.096
What are you like?

03:29.116 --> 03:30.578
What kind of fruit are you bearing?

03:31.099 --> 03:33.042
Good fruit encourages people.

03:33.262 --> 03:34.665
It builds other people up.

03:35.165 --> 03:37.149
It leads someone closer to Jesus.

03:37.750 --> 03:40.674
It creates unity instead of division.

03:42.457 --> 03:46.303
And there's that spiritual fruit, our connection with God.

03:47.004 --> 03:50.770
And when we are bearing fruit in that way,

03:51.106 --> 03:58.516
We maybe have this kind of stirring to pray a hunger for God's word.

03:58.636 --> 04:00.759
We just have to eat our Bible.

04:01.319 --> 04:09.290
And we trusting God in trials and difficult times, we stand firm in all the promises that we've sung about this morning.

04:10.171 --> 04:15.538
Maybe that inner connection with God is that obedience to follow his leading.

04:15.682 --> 04:17.645
All of that happens in a really deep way.

04:18.346 --> 04:22.051
All of those things are what fruit in our lives might look like.

04:23.093 --> 04:26.357
And they all start with the roots of our life.

04:27.459 --> 04:36.131
Just like a tree, a healthy tree depends on healthy, deep roots, where our roots are are really, really important.

04:36.211 --> 04:43.762
And over the past few weeks, we've been exploring what it means to be rooted, and we have focused.

04:44.194 --> 04:49.902
at looking at Jesus and the Word of God, being rooted there, being rooted in Him.

04:50.383 --> 04:55.751
We've looked at being rooted in community, gathering together as a church.

04:56.452 --> 05:11.474
We've looked at being rooted in deep spiritual friendships and looking to develop those in our lives because all of those things, like healthy trees, keep us rooted and growing healthy.

05:11.554 --> 05:12.856
There's an image of a tree.

05:12.976 --> 05:14.057
I love this image.

05:14.077 --> 05:24.111
A tree that is not struggling to survive, not barely hanging on, but planted, rooted, nourished, well-watered.

05:24.151 --> 05:29.458
That's when I read Psalm 1, the kind of tree I imagine.

05:29.598 --> 05:41.554
And that is my prayer and my hope for all of us as individuals that we will grow like that, healthy, strong, bearing fruit,

05:41.858 --> 05:43.762
or seeds in season.

05:44.062 --> 05:51.137
And today, I'm going to be talking about one of the key ways that with God's help, we deepen our roots.

05:52.099 --> 05:53.501
And it's about serving.

05:54.243 --> 05:57.690
So I'm going to go for serving with purpose this morning.

05:58.812 --> 06:03.762
So when I say the word serve, you might feel excited

06:03.842 --> 06:07.207
I don't know, you might feel a bit nervous, oh no.

06:07.868 --> 06:11.973
Or you might suddenly remember the email that you didn't reply to six months ago.

06:12.013 --> 06:13.475
It's okay.

06:15.999 --> 06:28.376
Here are a few, I'm gonna just go through some inspiring reasons that serving is really about developing healthy roots, developing healthy discipleship, okay?

06:28.937 --> 06:32.562
So, first of all, serving is at the heart

06:32.738 --> 06:33.879
of following Jesus.

06:34.961 --> 06:36.943
I want to start with the words of Jesus himself.

06:36.984 --> 06:38.085
You've got a sneak preview.

06:39.567 --> 06:48.679
So Mark 10, for even the son of man did not come to be served but to serve and give his life as a ransom for many.

06:49.840 --> 06:53.785
Jesus, the king of kings, didn't come demanding that people served him.

06:54.486 --> 06:55.568
He came to serve.

06:56.349 --> 07:00.434
He came, if you just think about what he did,

07:00.514 --> 07:02.437
He came washing feet.

07:03.018 --> 07:04.981
He came feeding crowds.

07:05.862 --> 07:09.427
He came touching the outcast and knows that no one else would go close to.

07:09.467 --> 07:13.012
He came laying down his life.

07:14.234 --> 07:20.123
In the kingdom of God, greatness is not about being served, but it is about serving.

07:21.084 --> 07:26.472
So if we're full as a Jesus Christ, serving isn't like this added extra.

07:27.073 --> 07:30.418
It's very, very much about following the lead of Jesus.

07:30.658 --> 07:32.261
who knows best for us.

07:32.803 --> 07:41.561
And being his disciple, being his apprentice, staying close to him is about doing what he does, being where he is.

07:42.122 --> 07:51.602
And if we are close to him, if we are rooted in his word and in his presence, just as someone talks about, then our response is born out of his love.

07:51.714 --> 07:56.859
It's an overflow of love that we are now aware of when we are rooted in Him.

07:57.360 --> 08:00.903
And the incredible thing is we begin to sort of love the things He loves.

08:01.424 --> 08:04.667
We begin to love those around us just that bit more.

08:05.368 --> 08:08.811
And serving, I believe, is an act of worship.

08:09.592 --> 08:19.122
You know, and it bubbles up and then we have to make a choice, but we are simply responding to the love He has lavished on us by loving others.

08:20.034 --> 08:22.777
serving is integral to following Jesus.

08:23.577 --> 08:28.923
And it's his way, that is a way of loving and humility and sacrifice.

08:29.663 --> 08:31.525
And so I think that's why it's one of these roots.

08:32.186 --> 08:48.882
When we serve others, as Jesus did, from a place of love, that we're not just doing a task, we're not just doing a job, we're not filling a rotor once a month, we give back to God, what he's given to us as we serve

08:49.122 --> 08:50.163
those around us.

08:50.524 --> 08:52.146
We respond to Christ's love.

08:52.527 --> 09:02.360
And the more we are invited to live this adventure of loving Him, receiving His love and responding day by day, becoming more like Him.

09:02.901 --> 09:07.727
Serving others is not something actually that our flesh would choose to do.

09:07.828 --> 09:18.482
Serving and being generous is a massive place, I think, where we experience a real battle about being generous and serving others.

09:18.946 --> 09:25.135
It can be so hard to be sacrificial and step outside of ourselves and look to someone else.

09:25.696 --> 09:31.565
But it's Christ deeply at work in us who draws us to step forward and to serve.

09:32.767 --> 09:41.980
And as we do, it's amazing roots go down and down because we grow in patience when we cooperate with the Holy Spirit.

09:42.561 --> 09:45.746
We grow in kindness when we respond to God.

09:46.082 --> 09:50.386
we grow to be more like Jesus when we stop and we put others first.

09:51.427 --> 09:58.334
And that's how healthy roots of faith and obedience go deeper and deeper over time.

09:59.876 --> 10:06.242
So, that first point I wanted to make was that serving is just at the heart of following Jesus.

10:06.803 --> 10:11.348
And as I was preparing this, I was thinking about Chelsea, who's gonna come and join me now.

10:11.728 --> 10:13.810
She's been in our church a little while and I thought,

10:13.890 --> 10:16.794
I'd love you to meet Chelsea and meet who she is.

10:17.234 --> 10:25.165
And I just want her to say a little bit about serving and what Jesus has done in her as she serves others.

10:25.445 --> 10:26.467
Say this is Chelsea.

10:26.587 --> 10:27.268
Who's a bit nervous?

10:27.528 --> 10:28.489
So please welcome her.

10:32.475 --> 10:32.815
Hello.

10:36.801 --> 10:36.921
Hi.

10:41.507 --> 10:43.890
I thought you were going to ask the questions first and then.

10:44.130 --> 10:44.991
I was going to answer them.

10:47.193 --> 10:49.175
The questions I sent Chelsea were this.

10:49.715 --> 10:53.399
How did you come to be here at Life Inyard and be grown in your faith?

10:54.059 --> 10:57.002
How does serving others look like in your life?

10:57.182 --> 11:02.307
And how has God moved in your life as you and Josh and Harry have stepped into serving?

11:03.208 --> 11:06.191
That's what I asked her.

11:06.211 --> 11:07.112
Just so I didn't ramble.

11:08.153 --> 11:13.458
We ended up at this church because Harry had learned about Jesus in an already lesson.

11:13.986 --> 11:15.307
That was pretty much it.

11:16.969 --> 11:20.753
Harry goes through phases sometimes, so we thought this was just another phase.

11:21.414 --> 11:25.979
Because Harry gets hyper-fogrissed because he's got autism and ADHD.

11:27.321 --> 11:30.404
So he kept going, I really love Jesus when he came home.

11:30.444 --> 11:32.726
And we were going, right, it's just a phase.

11:33.087 --> 11:34.428
He's gonna grow up, that's fine.

11:34.448 --> 11:35.990
And he didn't.

11:36.511 --> 11:38.513
He kept coming home going, I really, really like Jesus.

11:38.573 --> 11:39.874
I've learnt about his crucifixion.

11:39.894 --> 11:40.735
I'm really sad.

11:40.755 --> 11:43.378
I can't believe we did that to him.

11:43.810 --> 11:46.973
and he got really upset and then he learned that he rose again and he was very happy.

11:48.495 --> 11:51.619
So he started praying and mainly he started going right.

11:51.659 --> 11:54.081
We need to find a church because obviously this isn't going away.

11:55.042 --> 11:58.166
And we kept looking at different churches going, oh, this one's very dark.

11:58.206 --> 11:58.947
I don't like this one.

11:59.647 --> 12:01.389
And then he was going, oh, this one's very dusty.

12:01.409 --> 12:02.691
I'm not going at that one, man.

12:03.492 --> 12:10.219
So then we went to the park across the road and came in and cat offered him a drink of juice.

12:10.800 --> 12:12.882
And that city was over there.

12:13.026 --> 12:15.308
And he was like, Mom, I think this one's the one.

12:16.289 --> 12:19.753
And as well, if any said, Mom, I can feel Jesus here.

12:20.513 --> 12:22.976
So that is why we started coming to this church.

12:23.656 --> 12:29.882
And then after we listened to a few different Sunday services, we said, we're definitely coming back.

12:30.583 --> 12:31.764
So that's how we ended up here.

12:32.425 --> 12:37.130
And every time we listened, we felt like we're being cold to come back.

12:37.450 --> 12:38.571
And it started to make sense.

12:39.292 --> 12:41.714
So that was the reason why we ended up here.

12:41.954 --> 12:46.600
The second question was, how does saving look?

12:47.301 --> 12:49.364
How does saving others look in your life?

12:49.624 --> 12:54.291
So I help with the kids life one at five on a Sunday once a month.

12:55.332 --> 13:01.400
May and Josh help at the pantry and Friday lunch club and the warm welcome.

13:01.961 --> 13:05.065
So since helping one at fives I've learned quite a lot.

13:06.307 --> 13:08.951
That actually teach me quite a bit.

13:09.812 --> 13:11.474
They're very, very welcoming.

13:11.810 --> 13:14.934
and they come up with some crazy things, but in a good way.

13:15.935 --> 13:22.724
They've encouraged me to be very, very open about my faith, because when I was new to it, I was quite shy, especially about praying out loud.

13:23.525 --> 13:28.852
As soon as they hear the worship music, they'd get right in their way straight away, like, come on Chelsea, let's dance.

13:29.553 --> 13:30.634
And I'm like, oh, really?

13:31.295 --> 13:31.876
Like, come on.

13:32.757 --> 13:40.146
And when I heard Minay getting up off the floor, it was actually Joy, who came over and was like,

13:40.354 --> 13:41.535
we can pray for new knees.

13:42.777 --> 13:45.880
In straight away, I've had a hand over my knee going, let's pray.

13:45.920 --> 13:47.882
So I prayed about my knee.

13:48.923 --> 13:53.509
And she was about three, yeah, at the time, when she was praying for the knee.

13:55.030 --> 13:55.751
No, it was dry.

13:57.653 --> 14:01.017
So that was very surprising at the time, because she's very small.

14:01.918 --> 14:05.662
And the other thing, when I was asked about praying, I said, so how do you use pray?

14:05.742 --> 14:06.483
One more colouring in.

14:07.184 --> 14:09.266
I just speak to him like he's your best friend.

14:09.570 --> 14:10.992
You know, like, I should already know that.

14:12.014 --> 14:14.819
And at the pantry, no one is rushed.

14:15.380 --> 14:17.183
And that was the other thing I found very helpful.

14:17.764 --> 14:20.308
As a volunteer in other places, it's always been a job.

14:20.789 --> 14:21.870
You just get on with your job.

14:22.051 --> 14:24.415
And quick as you can, they're just a number, get them in, get them out.

14:25.016 --> 14:33.650
Here, if people come in with the weight of the world on their shoulders and they feel really, really downtrodden, everyone is told just

14:33.826 --> 14:41.876
Make everyone feel welcome if they've got something to say, sit and chat with them, have a cup of tea, and those people you feel are so much better, and I've never felt that anywhere else.

14:42.597 --> 14:43.498
So that's really good.

14:44.739 --> 14:46.321
So that's deep in my faith quite a lot.

14:46.421 --> 14:47.422
I've been taught quite a lot.

14:48.644 --> 14:54.651
And the last one was, how was God deep in your faith as me and Josh have stepped into saving?

14:54.991 --> 14:56.854
Josh's confidence has really improved.

14:57.214 --> 14:59.257
I'm going to mention you.

14:59.897 --> 15:03.762
Josh doesn't like, well, doesn't like speaking to a lot of people.

15:03.906 --> 15:08.093
Josh is also autistic, sorry to mention that.

15:08.914 --> 15:11.018
But he feels like this is his church family too.

15:11.799 --> 15:13.021
And he's just started alpha.

15:13.983 --> 15:17.328
And when he came home, he decided to talk till half 11 at night.

15:17.568 --> 15:19.071
And I kept having to say it's bedtime.

15:19.091 --> 15:20.934
We've got to go to sleep now, Josh.

15:20.994 --> 15:23.719
So I think we've both grown very spiritually.

15:24.079 --> 15:25.301
And I think that's helped us there.

15:25.321 --> 15:28.306
And so there you go.

15:36.322 --> 15:41.592
I remember Chelsea sharing a testimony at her baptism and I'm like, she's so good at communicating.

15:41.632 --> 15:42.755
I'm going to get her to share.

15:43.396 --> 15:46.903
So the first thing is that it is at the heart of following Jesus.

15:46.963 --> 15:49.808
The second thing is everyone gets to play.

15:49.828 --> 15:52.754
One of our core values as a church is very simple.

15:52.962 --> 15:54.304
Everyone gets to play.

15:54.685 --> 15:57.350
There are no spectators in the body of Christ.

15:57.730 --> 15:59.494
There are no VIP Christians.

15:59.814 --> 16:04.563
There are no professional ministers who do everything and serve while everyone else watches on.

16:04.863 --> 16:06.406
That is not how things work.

16:06.947 --> 16:17.746
One Peter 4.10 says, each of you should use whatever gift you have received to serve others as faithful stewards of God's grace in its barriers form.

16:18.082 --> 16:24.452
Each of you, not some of you, not the confident ones, not the outgoing ones, not the ones who have been here for years.

16:24.512 --> 16:26.895
Each of you, each of you.

16:27.136 --> 16:28.317
God has placed gifts.

16:28.478 --> 16:28.998
I love this.

16:29.259 --> 16:30.380
He has placed gifts.

16:30.461 --> 16:31.582
He has placed passions.

16:31.883 --> 16:36.830
He has placed abilities and different personality in every person in this room.

16:37.892 --> 16:39.374
And he did that on purpose.

16:40.335 --> 16:44.722
You have been created just like you are.

16:44.834 --> 16:47.298
And Josh cooks amazing food.

16:47.458 --> 16:48.980
I don't know if you've written it down here as well.

16:49.481 --> 17:01.239
He cooks amazing food and joyfully cleans the kitchen till it's spotless and leaves on a Sunday sometimes at four or five o'clock because he has got it sparkling.

17:01.359 --> 17:02.601
And it's joyful when he does it.

17:03.883 --> 17:05.846
Joy, she's, yeah, there she is.

17:06.446 --> 17:07.829
She's stripy top.

17:08.109 --> 17:09.191
That's joy with the baby.

17:09.511 --> 17:11.474
She has this gentle,

17:11.586 --> 17:18.134
amazing way of connecting with people and sending an encouraging text at just the right time.

17:19.716 --> 17:22.399
She sends Bible verses and she says, I'm praying for you.

17:23.100 --> 17:30.769
Adam bashes the drums with more joy than anyone I know and serves us by helping us lead worship.

17:32.712 --> 17:38.058
Sarah fills up the coffee and trundles through with the trolley and she does it.

17:38.118 --> 17:38.779
She loves it.

17:39.720 --> 17:41.202
There are so many people.

17:41.346 --> 17:42.948
who serve in different ways.

17:43.049 --> 17:48.777
When everyone plays their part in the body of Christ, the church is just so beautiful.

17:49.859 --> 17:56.609
A tree bears fruit because branches are designed to bear fruit, and it plays its part in the healthy tree.

17:57.169 --> 18:03.058
And in God's family, and of course there are ways to serve outside of the church,

18:03.202 --> 18:09.437
And Bible's clear, there's talk of serving each other as God's family in the church and serving the world.

18:09.457 --> 18:12.243
Those two things are equally as important.

18:13.607 --> 18:15.090
We can serve our neighbors.

18:15.330 --> 18:26.863
We went, we've had elderly neighbors, less than one of them has Parkinson's and we went and put their Christmas tree up me and Sarah, I think it was just before Christmas and then we went and packed it away and took the boxes upstairs.

18:27.224 --> 18:32.350
There are so many ways to practically serve out your neighbors, whoever your neighbors are.

18:32.830 --> 18:39.418
Our families, sometimes we just serve our families because that is where God has placed us and that's what we need to do.

18:40.940 --> 18:42.962
But in this church, everyone

18:43.042 --> 18:45.244
gets to play, you get to play.

18:46.225 --> 18:47.327
And here's the beautiful thing.

18:47.587 --> 18:49.329
You don't have to know what your gifts are.

18:49.589 --> 18:52.472
You don't have to know how brilliant you are before you start serving.

18:52.833 --> 18:59.400
You often discover your gifts when you start stepping in, just I think as Chelsea's just mentioned there.

19:00.681 --> 19:08.369
And I think often what we're drawn to, what we're interested to gives us clues maybe about how God has made us and how he's made us to step in.

19:09.591 --> 19:10.612
But just try something.

19:11.152 --> 19:12.594
You learn, you grow,

19:12.674 --> 19:20.268
You find your place, you're connected with more and more other brothers and sisters who will encourage you on.

19:20.348 --> 19:25.577
And you meet Jesus as you express practically God's love through serving in some way.

19:25.797 --> 19:30.205
That's how roots go deep by being planted and having a try.

19:30.426 --> 19:31.768
Jump in, try something.

19:32.570 --> 19:35.615
So serving is the heart at the heart of following Jesus.

19:36.156 --> 19:37.298
Everyone gets to play.

19:37.410 --> 19:40.855
And I would love to invite you as well to step towards that today.

19:41.195 --> 19:50.528
Later on, there's a slide that will be on, and you can just click and just say, well, I'd like to try serving here or there, and we'd love to help you with that.

19:51.569 --> 19:56.596
And even if you've only been here a few weeks, that's you as well, okay?

19:56.616 --> 20:03.786
Thirdly, serving roots us in God because it connects us to our God-given purpose.

20:03.806 --> 20:06.930
I've just kind of alluded to it, but Ephesians 2,

20:07.554 --> 20:12.220
8 to 10 says, for it is by grace that you have been saved through faith.

20:12.641 --> 20:14.323
And this is not from yourselves.

20:14.483 --> 20:18.488
It is a gift of God, not by works so that no one can boast.

20:19.009 --> 20:27.240
For we are God's handiwork created in Christ Jesus to do good works, which God prepared in advance for us to do.

20:27.280 --> 20:31.486
We have good works to do.

20:32.787 --> 20:34.770
But more than that,

20:35.202 --> 20:40.709
God created these good works in mind.

20:41.531 --> 20:44.454
They're prepared in advance for us to do.

20:44.515 --> 20:52.926
My recent Google search yesterday informed me that there are 8.3 billion humans on the planet.

20:54.228 --> 21:04.882
And you know what's incredible about that is that nobody else in that whole 8.3 billion can do the things that God made you

21:05.026 --> 21:05.467
to do.

21:05.487 --> 21:17.887
8.3 billion, you are fearfully, wonderfully made a masterpiece with works that he has prepared in advance for you to do.

21:18.347 --> 21:19.890
You said you wanted a word this morning.

21:19.910 --> 21:22.053
I feel like that's God's word to you, is this telling me?

21:23.135 --> 21:25.499
You are one in 8.3 billion.

21:25.839 --> 21:30.988
He's made you to bring all that you are, to serve him and bless others.

21:31.128 --> 21:32.530
And only you can do that.

21:32.770 --> 21:34.332
You are unique.

21:34.472 --> 21:35.613
My dad has a twin brother.

21:35.633 --> 21:37.515
He's even different from his brother.

21:38.155 --> 21:38.836
You're unique.

21:38.876 --> 21:41.178
There is no one in all creation like you.

21:41.198 --> 21:46.864
There's no one who can express his love in this world and serve others like you.

21:46.904 --> 21:51.989
No one can glorify God.

21:53.611 --> 21:57.935
That is our purpose to worship God and to glorify him.

21:58.696 --> 22:00.818
No one can make God's scene

22:00.898 --> 22:03.543
glorify him in the way that you can.

22:04.085 --> 22:06.750
You are beyond special.

22:07.191 --> 22:08.293
You are priceless.

22:08.834 --> 22:11.319
You are unique, made for a purpose.

22:16.350 --> 22:17.412
See, are you hearing me?

22:18.394 --> 22:18.775
Okay.

22:19.817 --> 22:20.338
Good.

22:21.186 --> 22:41.020
different gifts, different personalities, different ways of supporting the children in the kids' ministry, different ways of serving the youth, different ways of making meals, different ways of leading worship, different ways of speaking, different ways of just doing it all that goes on in our world, in our church.

22:42.562 --> 22:46.248
It's all different.

22:46.268 --> 22:47.250
Serving isn't

22:48.738 --> 22:50.460
just about what happens to be gathered.

22:50.480 --> 22:54.705
Like I said, it's about who we are in the world, who we come into contact with as well.

22:55.146 --> 23:00.452
The different ways we can serve our neighbors, our work colleagues, our friends and strangers.

23:01.894 --> 23:06.941
We all have opportunities to serve as Jesus would have us serve.

23:09.323 --> 23:11.686
But we get to choose how we respond.

23:12.347 --> 23:17.874
Do we cooperate with that truth and with his invitation or not?

23:18.786 --> 23:25.875
we are called as followers of Jesus created by God to serve others throughout our lives.

23:29.419 --> 23:33.364
When we serve, we reflect God's grace to those around us.

23:35.566 --> 23:38.550
And I know our lives can look different.

23:38.570 --> 23:45.138
We go through different seasons and some will be called to care and serve their family.

23:45.250 --> 23:51.498
or poorly relatives, and they need to focus their energy on serving their family for a season.

23:51.958 --> 23:53.160
And that is what is needed.

23:53.260 --> 24:04.114
And God knows those people who are serving in hidden ways, their families, you are serving the Lord, you are glorifying God as you do that.

24:05.876 --> 24:13.906
So if you're here as well, and you actually really need to be served, you know, you're carrying heavy weights and

24:14.242 --> 24:15.684
You need help.

24:15.924 --> 24:17.246
You need to be served.

24:18.108 --> 24:20.451
That sounds like being part of a family.

24:20.831 --> 24:22.934
And I'm really glad that you're here.

24:23.675 --> 24:25.158
So let us serve you as well.

24:27.561 --> 24:32.268
Serving in all its forms shifts the focus from ourselves to others.

24:32.508 --> 24:34.691
And we embody Christ as we do it.

24:34.931 --> 24:42.322
It's not merely an action, but it's the heart posture where we put down roots over and over.

24:43.266 --> 24:46.029
Galatians, his three verses, I want to read you quickly.

24:46.330 --> 24:57.083
Galatians 3, 13 says, you, my brothers and sisters, were called to be free, but do not use your freedom to indulge the flesh, rather serve one another humbly in love.

24:57.964 --> 25:00.027
Mark 10, 45, we heard it already.

25:00.067 --> 25:06.275
For even the son of man did not come to be served, but to serve and to give his life as a ransom for many.

25:06.896 --> 25:12.082
Philippians 2, 4, let each of you look not only to his own interests,

25:12.226 --> 25:13.970
but to the interests of others.

25:15.093 --> 25:17.197
So we are designed with a purpose.

25:17.258 --> 25:22.770
We are created to serve when we humble ourselves to serve whatever that looks like.

25:23.512 --> 25:29.085
Given of our time, our energy, our resources to serve, there is life in that.

25:29.686 --> 25:31.410
We're made to do that.

25:31.650 --> 25:37.697
I was on a Zoom call a while ago with a pastor from Canada called David Ruis.

25:37.718 --> 25:38.579
He's a songwriter.

25:38.619 --> 25:41.242
We don't sing his songs, I'm sure, from time to time.

25:41.682 --> 25:46.809
And he leads the Association of Vineyard Churches in the whole of Canada.

25:47.369 --> 25:53.557
And he said, I never want to graduate from place, from position of servant.

25:54.118 --> 25:56.481
I never want to graduate from position of servant.

25:56.841 --> 25:57.522
I'm like, yeah.

25:57.602 --> 25:58.203
Me too.

25:58.643 --> 26:00.406
Never want to graduate from that place.

26:00.526 --> 26:01.407
Jesus didn't.

26:01.988 --> 26:03.309
Why on earth would we?

26:03.350 --> 26:07.815
And that's phrase stuck with me.

26:08.456 --> 26:13.863
I want my life inside and outside to be growing more and more like Jesus.

26:15.646 --> 26:22.034
And a lot of people, and I certainly can can say, I grew most in my faith when I started serving.

26:22.626 --> 26:25.969
There's a beautiful kingdom blessing in serving others.

26:26.069 --> 26:33.817
Chelsea mentioned a little bit how the children, as she literally knelt with them, arrived early, cleared up all the crumbs for whatever.

26:34.177 --> 26:39.102
She is blessed when she serves the children because it's faith in action.

26:39.282 --> 26:41.104
And Jesus loves that.

26:42.385 --> 26:51.154
In this context on a Sunday morning, for example, serving people stepping forward and playing their part means children feel safe and loved.

26:51.394 --> 27:07.230
guests feel welcomed, corporate worship becomes possible, community is built, the gospel is made visible, meals are shared, people are ministered to by God as we pray for one another and church family continues to grow, just to name a few.

27:07.270 --> 27:10.853
But serving blesses the one who serves as well.

27:11.434 --> 27:19.762
God will grow you, he will grow me just as deeply rooted trees grow and bear fruit in season.

27:21.186 --> 27:28.195
So yeah, there's no guilt, there's no pressure, just an opportunity to step closer today, to serve in some way.

27:28.656 --> 27:33.302
There are as many opportunities as there are people in this room.

27:33.643 --> 27:34.664
Everyone gets to play.

27:35.445 --> 27:42.254
Whoever you are, I want to invite you to come and to serve in this body, the church.

27:43.015 --> 27:47.021
That's God's vision for you in the church and outside of the church.

27:47.441 --> 27:50.866
So I'm just extending that invitation to you.

27:51.010 --> 27:54.415
So I am going to pray for us.

27:54.435 --> 28:02.286
A few people over the past couple of days have just been sending words and pictures last week as we minister to one another.

28:02.326 --> 28:05.431
There was a real freedom as the Holy Spirit came.

28:05.931 --> 28:09.977
And I don't know about everything I've said has struck you today.

28:10.017 --> 28:16.146
But shall we just respond to God, whatever he might want to

28:16.258 --> 28:17.139
say to you.

28:17.159 --> 28:26.288
In fact, before you stand, I'm just going to read to you a couple of things that people have sent me in terms of words and pictures, because we believe God speaks.

28:26.888 --> 28:30.512
And so, Mary, did you have something you wanted to share?

28:32.253 --> 28:33.535
Yeah, come on.

28:33.555 --> 28:35.597
So, yes, this was about roots.

28:36.017 --> 28:45.426
So this maybe isn't connected with what I've just said, but someone said they felt like God is saying that people are living shallow lives, that their roots might be spread wide, but they're

28:45.538 --> 28:47.201
only just below the surface.

28:47.401 --> 28:51.227
And when pushed or strained, they bend rather than stand firm.

28:51.287 --> 28:57.837
And that maybe people justify their actions and compare them to the world rather than up to the word.

28:59.219 --> 29:03.285
And he wants us to be in this world, but not of this world.

29:03.646 --> 29:10.456
So we need to push our roots deeper so that we don't bend when we're tested and compromise.

29:11.899 --> 29:14.162
And Mary had something she wanted to share as well.

29:17.730 --> 29:22.919
Yes, over the last few weeks I've just had this picture going through my mind of a piece of knitting actually.

29:22.959 --> 29:29.269
And it was green and I was asking God about why was it green and I think it's because it represents life.

29:30.731 --> 29:44.594
But the knitting had a stitch that had dropped and I just felt that God was saying that sometimes we need to pick up within ourselves what that might be that God wants us to do.

29:44.770 --> 29:52.198
But just as with this jumper, you can see this side here, but the underneath side is just as important.

29:52.798 --> 30:00.626
So it may be that the ways that we're giving are serving or hidden, but that's just as important to God.

30:00.886 --> 30:06.632
So it might be something hidden like prayer or helping somebody that maybe nobody else knows about, but God knows.

30:07.493 --> 30:12.338
And I felt that he was saying, you know, that each part as we play our part,

30:12.546 --> 30:15.028
That's what holds the whole garment together.

30:15.068 --> 30:20.713
And I've just been kind of struck also by Nicola's top that she's wearing today with all the beautiful colors.

30:21.274 --> 30:27.259
And I just felt God was speaking to me about how every different color makes the garment so beautiful.

30:28.561 --> 30:30.823
And because we all have something different to contribute.

30:32.344 --> 30:33.125
Thanks very much.

30:33.145 --> 30:38.510
Okay, well, let's just stand and respond to what Holy Spirit might be doing.

30:39.931 --> 30:41.012
Calm Holy Spirit.

